        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "Run memory flush before preflight compaction",
        "body": "Fixes #84695.\n\n## Summary\n\n- Run automatic memory flush before preflight compaction in `runReplyAgent`.\n- Keep visible memory-flush errors on the same pre-run return path before the main reply.\n- Add regression coverage proving memory flush is invoked before preflight compaction.\n\n## What Problem This Solves\n\n`runReplyAgent` must run the memory-flush phase before preflight compaction so durable memory has a chance to run before aggressive transcript reduction. Before this PR, preflight compaction could run first and reduce transcript context before the automatic memory flush path had a chance to preserve it.\n\n## Evidence\n\n- Real environment tested: isolated worktree `/private/tmp/openclaw-pr84792-proof-rebase-20260630`, rebased onto current `origin/main` `d68ba5edc59`, PR head `8c816b184195db99570e124e649f39f8b0e8e237`, Node `v24.18.0`.\n- Exact proof command:\n\n```sh\nOPENCLAW_DIAGNOSTICS=1 \\\nOPENCLAW_DIAGNOSTICS_TIMELINE_PATH=/tmp/openclaw-84792-rebased-timeline.jsonl \\\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-direct-runtime-config.test.ts -- \\\n  -t 'resolves direct reply runs before early helpers read config'\n```\n\n- Parsed diagnostics proof:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"ok\": true,\n  \"head\": \"8c816b184195db99570e124e649f39f8b0e8e237\",\n  \"timelinePath\": \"/tmp/openclaw-84792-rebased-timeline.jsonl\",\n  \"phaseStartOrder\": [\n    \"reply.memory_flush\",\n    \"reply.preflight_compaction\"\n  ],\n  \"relevantEvents\": [\n    {\n      \"type\": \"span.start\",\n      \"name\": \"reply.memory_flush\",\n      \"phase\": \"agent-turn\",\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-07-01T05:08:39.377Z\",\n      \"attributes\": {\n        \"provider\": \"openai\",\n        \"hasSessionKey\": true,\n        \"isHeartbeat\": false,\n        \"queueMode\": \"interrupt\",\n        \"isActive\": false,\n        \"blockStreamingEnabled\": false\n      }\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"span.end\",\n      \"name\": \"reply.memory_flush\",\n      \"phase\": \"agent-turn\",\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-07-01T05:08:39.378Z\",\n      \"durationMs\": 0.613\n    },\n    {\n      \"type\": \"span.start\",\n      \"name\": \"reply.preflight_compaction\",\n      \"phase\": \"agent-turn\",\n      \"timestamp\": \"2026-07-01T05:08:39.378Z\",\n      \"attributes\": {\n        \"provider\": \"openai\",\n        \"hasSessionKey\": true,\n        \"isHeartbeat\": false,\n        \"queueMode\": \"interrupt\",\n        \"isActive\": false,\n        \"blockStreamingEnabled\": false\n      }\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: the diagnostics timeline for the rebased PR head starts `reply.memory_flush` before `reply.preflight_compaction`, proving the pre-run maintenance order is flush first, then compaction.\n\nWhat was not tested: no external provider turn was executed; the proof intentionally stops at the preflight compaction sentinel after exercising the real `runReplyAgent` pre-run maintenance path.\n\n## Verification\n\n```text\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-direct-runtime-config.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-memory.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/reply-state.test.ts\nTest Files  3 passed (3)\nTests  92 passed (92)\n\nnode node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner.ts src/auto-reply/reply/agent-runner-direct-runtime-config.test.ts\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n\npnpm check:test-types\n# passed\n\npnpm lint\n# passed\n\ngit diff --check origin/main...HEAD\n# clean\n```\n",
